#compdef hxnamespace hxnormalize hxpipe hxprintlinks hxprune hxref hxremove hxrmlf hxsel hxstrip hxtoc hxuncdata hxunent hxunicode hxunpipe hxunxmlns hxwls hxxmlns

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1

case $service in
  (hxnamespace)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-d[delete the namespace]' \
      '-l[give line numbers in error messages]' \
      '*:input HTML/XML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxnormalize)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-l+[wrap output at column]:n:' \
      '-d[output document model in DTD form]' \
      '-e[output as XML]' \
      '-i[indent output]' \
      '-s[strip whitespace]' \
      '-t[transform tags to lower-case]' \
      '-x[output as XHTML]' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxpipe)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-c+[catalog file]:file:_files' \
      '-l+[give line numbers in error messages]:n:' \
      '*:input XML file:_files -g "*.(xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxprintlinks)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-b+[base URL]:url:' \
      '-l[print line and column numbers]' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxprune)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-c+[CSS class to keep visible]:class:' \
      '-i+[ID to keep visible]:id:' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxref)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-x[generate XML output]' \
      '-l+[file with line of links]:file:_files' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxremove)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-l[give line numbers in error messages]' \
      '*:CSS selector:' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxrmlf)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '*:input file:_files' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxsel)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-c[print contents of matching elements]' \
      '-i+[case-insensitive selector]:selector:' \
      '-l[print line and column numbers]' \
      '-s+[separator between matched elements]:string:' \
      '*:CSS selector:' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxstrip)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-l[give line numbers in error messages]' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxtoc)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-d[generate links from headings to TOC entries]' \
      '-l+[lowest level to include]:n:' \
      '-t+[CSS class for TOC]:class:' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxuncdata|hxunent|hxunicode|hxunxmlns|hxxmlns)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '*:input file:_files' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxunpipe)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-l+[give line numbers in error messages]:n:' \
      '*:pipe-format input:_files' && ret=0
    ;;
  (hxwls)
    _arguments -s -S \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '-b+[base URL]:url:' \
      '-l[print line and column numbers]' \
      '*:input HTML file:_files -g "*.(html|htm|xml|xhtml)"' && ret=0
    ;;
  (*)
    _arguments \
      '-h[show help]' \
      '*:input file:_files' && ret=0
    ;;
esac

return ret
